"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Moses was shy of public speaking</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10-Exod4:15\">EXO 4:10–4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:12\">EXO 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:30\">EXO 6:30</a></p>\n<h2>Shyness caused by youth and inexperience</h2>\n<h3>Jeremiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:6\">JER 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Timothy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:10-1Cor16:11\">1CO 16:10–16:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:12\">1TI 4:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:7\">2TI 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The woman subject to bleeding was shy of making herself known</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:28\">MRK 5:25–5:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:33\">MRK 5:33</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ taught his disciples not to be shy of bearing witness to him</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:14-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:14–5:16</a></p>",
